Preheat oven to 400 degrees F and grease cookie sheets. Cream butter. Add eggs, sugar and vanilla. Mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients. Stir until well blended. Cut dough into pieces about 2 inches by 2 inches. Dip in white sugar. Roll dough into palm of hand until round. Dip in brown sugar and place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Bake at 400 degrees F for about 10 minutes or until light brown.